Round 1
[Patient] What foods can I eat to help my heart failure?
[Educator] Choose fresh fruits, veggies, whole grains, lean proteins, and low-sodium options.

Round 2
[Patient] Should I avoid any specific foods?
[Educator] Limit salt, processed foods, sugary drinks, and fatty meats to help your heart.

Round 3
[Patient] Can I still have my favorite soul food dishes?
[Educator] You can still enjoy soul food, just make healthier swaps like baked instead of fried.

Round 4
[Patient] Are there any herbs or spices that are good for heart health?
[Educator] Cinnamon, garlic, and turmeric are great for heart health and can add flavor to dishes.

Round 5
[Patient] What about drinks? Can I still have my sweet tea?
[Educator] Limit sugary drinks like sweet tea. Opt for water, herbal teas, or unsweetened beverages.

Round 6
[Patient] I love eating out, any tips for making healthier choices?
[Educator] Look for items with grilled or steamed options, and ask for dressings and sauces on the side.

Round 7
[Patient] What are some heart-friendly snacks I can have?
[Educator] Try nuts, seeds, yogurt, fruit, or whole grain crackers for heart-healthy snack options.

Round 8
[Patient] Can I still have dessert sometimes?
[Educator] Treat yourself in moderation with fruit, dark chocolate, or a small portion of a favorite dessert.

